&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This guide describes how you can monitor and debug your AWS Lambda functions with &lt;a href="https://thundra.io">Thundra&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="integrating-thundra-with-localstack">Integrating Thundra with LocalStack&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
&lt;h4 class="alert-heading">Supported languages&lt;/h4>
Currently only &lt;strong>Node.js&lt;/strong>, &lt;strong>Python&lt;/strong> and &lt;strong>Java&lt;/strong> Lambdas are supported in this integration - support for other runtimes (.NET, Go) is coming soon.
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>LocalStack comes with out-of-the-box support for Thundra. Simply obtain a Thundra API key &lt;a href="https://console.thundra.io/onboarding/serverless">here&lt;/a> and add it to your Lambda function&amp;rsquo;s environment variables (&lt;code>THUNDRA_APIKEY&lt;/code>):&lt;/p>
